N2  - Most casualty insurance loss reserving has been performed on a ?case basis? without regard to the causal factors which affect losses?accident frequency, accident severity, and the firm's exposure to claims. Here, a control approach is developed which permits the loss reserve decision-maker to establish loss reserves on the basis of these indicators of the current loss environment.
